<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="374" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1451073541" country="India" location="Viraktamath" municipality="Mohan" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" specimenCount="3" stateProvince="Yunnan Province" typeStatus="paratype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on two male specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion box="[1230,1433,151,176]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[151,515,188,213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. &amp; Mohan (2004) A revision of the deltocephaline genus Scaphoideus (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) from the Indian subcontinent. Zootaxa, 578, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="2004">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039582759E199F08FF5DFA10135D1A54:8EE365B89E189F08FF5DFF16136D1BE4" box="[151,289,188,213]" country="India" municipality="Mohan" name="Viraktamath" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" stateProvince="Yunnan Province">Viraktamath</location>
and 
<collectingMunicipality box="[350,429,188,213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">Mohan</collectingMunicipality>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[643,908,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculatus">
<emphasis box="[643,908,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">Scaphoideus spiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[984,1044,188,213]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">India</collectingCountry>
, which is treated here as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Li" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" box="[299,637,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yingjiangensis">
<emphasis box="[299,493,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">S. yingjiangensis</emphasis>
Wang &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
based on examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[990,1086,224,248]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">paratype</typeStatus>
male and additional material. Although the aedeagus of the 
<typeStatus box="[488,586,260,285]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[642,738,261,285]" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[777,919,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculatus">
<emphasis box="[777,919,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">S. spiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in the shape, there are a few specimens sharing variation in the form of the dorsal apodeme and curvature of the shaft collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[1206,1273,295,320]" name="China" pageId="23" pageNumber="374">China</collectingCountry>
and hence the synonymy.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
